Release Notes - Phoenix - Version 4.4.0

** New Feature
    * [PHOENIX-971] - Query server
    * [PHOENIX-1071] - Provide integration for exposing Phoenix tables as Spark RDDs
    * [PHOENIX-1452] - Add Phoenix client-side logging and capture resource utilization metrics
    * [PHOENIX-1609] - MR job to populate index tables 
    * [PHOENIX-1807] - Support UNION queries in subquery
    * [PHOENIX-1815] - Use Spark Data Source API in phoenix-spark module

** Improvement
    * [PHOENIX-39] - Add sustained load tester that measures throughput
    * [PHOENIX-1580] - Support UNION ALL
    * [PHOENIX-1653] - Allow option to pass peer zookeeper address to load data into a target cluster in Map Reduce api
    * [PHOENIX-1722] - Speedup CONVERT_TZ function
    * [PHOENIX-1746] - Pass through guidepost config params on UPDATE STATISTICS call
    * [PHOENIX-1756] - Add Month() and Second() built-in functions
    * [PHOENIX-1759] - PhoenixArray to have decent .toString() implementation.
    * [PHOENIX-1770] - psql.py returns 0 even if an error has occurred
    * [PHOENIX-1779] - Parallelize fetching of next batch of records for scans corresponding to queries with no order by 
    * [PHOENIX-1781] - Add Now()
    * [PHOENIX-1792] - Add Week() and Hour() built-ins
    * [PHOENIX-1799] - Provide parameter metadata for prepared create table statements
    * [PHOENIX-1934] - queryserver support for Windows service descriptor

** Task
    * [PHOENIX-538] - Support UDFs
    * [PHOENIX-1826] - Implement TrackOrderPreservingExpressionCompiler as Expression visitor instead of ParseNode visitor

** Sub-task
    * [PHOENIX-1060] - Replace ReferencingColumn with ColumnReference
